-\frac{2}{3}\dot{\phi}^{2}\left[\dot{\phi}\left(\sqrt{6}\dot{\chi}
-9H\right)-3\ddot{\phi} 
\right]\mathcal{G}_{B}
{\nonumber}\\
&&\!\!
+\frac{1}{2}e^{-\sqrt{\frac{2}{3}}\chi}\left[\dot{B}\dot{{\phi}}\mathcal{
G}_{B}+ \frac{{\phi}}{2} +\dot{{\phi}}^{2}\left(\mathcal{G}_{{\phi}}-2\mathcal{K}_{B} \right)
 \right],
 \end{eqnarray}
\begin{eqnarray}
\label{pDE}
&&\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!
p_{DE}\equiv  
 \frac{1}{2}\dot{\chi}^{2}+\frac{1}{4}e^{-2\sqrt{
\frac{2}{3}}
\chi}\mathcal{K}
{\nonumber}\\
&&\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!
+
\frac{1}{2} e^{-\sqrt{\frac{2}{3}}\chi}\left(\dot{B}\dot{{\phi}
}\mathcal{
G}_{B}+\dot{{\phi}}^{2}\mathcal{G}_{{\phi}}-\frac{{\phi}}{2} \right).
\end{eqnarray}
Therefore, in the new gravitational scalar-tensor theories at hand, we obtain an 
effective dark-energy sector that consists of both extra scalar degrees of freedom. 
Using the scalar field equations of motion (\ref{chiequation}) and (\ref{phiequation}), 
one can straightforwardly see that

